---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Professional Reflection" activeTab="uni">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4 text-industrial-black">Professional Reflection</h1>
        <p class="text-order-3 text-brand-purple tracking-[0.4em]">Internship Evaluation & Career Trajectory</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-24 pb-32">
        
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-purple mb-12">01 // Expectations vs. Reality</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="text-order-3 text-slate-400">Initial Expectations</h3>
                    <p class="text-order-2 italic border-l-2 border-slate-200 pl-6 text-lg">
                        "I suppose I expected the work to include elements of hands-on experience, the other workers to be friendly, and that this would be a great opportunity to expand my knowledge to further my career".
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="text-order-3 text-slate-400">The Reality</h3>
                    <p class="text-order-2">
                        The reality did not differ much from my expectations, though there was a larger volume of paperwork than initially anticipated. The working environment was more welcoming and less daunting than expected, with a high degree of friendliness among colleagues.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white/50 p-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-orange mb-12">02 // Core Industrial Lessons</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-4 text-industrial-black">Adaptability & Management</h3>
                    <p class="text-order-2">
                        The most important lessons involved being open to change and adaptable; when things do not go perfectly to plan, an engineer must be able to manage the task effectively regardless of project derailment.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-4 text-industrial-black">Effective Communication</h3>
                    <p class="text-order-2">
                        Being communicative is vital to prevent misunderstandings that lead to confusion and project risk. Clear communication builds better team relationships and makes the environment more comfortable for addressing issues.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black mb-12">03 // Value Proposition</h2>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black uppercase text-slate-800 mb-12 leading-tight">
                "A versatile, process-oriented technical resource with the capacity to quickly learn new systems and translate complex engineering knowledge into clear, accessible documentation".
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-6 text-order-3 text-slate-500">
                <p class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">•</span> Process Improvement: Reformatting customer records into traceability tables in Excel.</p>
                <p class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">•</span> Systems Implementation: Leading discussions on the rollout of Autodesk Vault Pro.</p>
                <p class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">•</span> Technical Writing: Authoring user manuals for the Schenck Balancing rotor and centrifuge stripping.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-purple mb-12">04 // Career Influence & Trajectory</h2>
            <p class="text-order-2 text-lg mb-12">
                The internship confirmed my interest in hands-on mechanical design while revealing a strength in engineering process management. 
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
                <ul class="space-y-4 border-t border-slate-200 pt-8">
                    <li class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black mb-2">Technical Exposure</li>
                    <li class="text-order-3 text-slate-500">• CAD Modeling: 1038 Press Shaft Bullnose</li>
                    <li class="text-order-3 text-slate-500">• Workshop: Observing tallow centrifuge stripping</li>
                    <li class="text-order-3 text-slate-500">• Testing: Gearboxes and bearings</li>
                </ul>
                <ul class="space-y-4 border-t border-slate-200 pt-8">
                    <li class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black mb-2">Process Ownership</li>
                    <li class="text-order-3 text-slate-500">• Manuals: Balancing machine user guides</li>
                    <li class="text-order-3 text-slate-500">• Templates: Customer evaluation reports</li>
                    <li class="text-order-3 text-slate-500">• Project Oversight: 1800 Cooker Wear Sleeves</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t-4 border-industrial-black pt-24">
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-purple mb-12">05 // Internal Audit & Peer Feedback</h2>
            <div class="bg-white/50 p-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
                <p class="text-order-2 italic mb-12 text-lg text-slate-600">
                    "Reflecting on my collaboration with Olivia, Muhaimin, and Eric, our team focused on the mechanical structure of a mechatronic system. Key takeaways included the importance of bridging the gap between technical CAD modeling and cost-effective material procurement."
                </p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black mb-4">Technical Integration</h4>
                        <p class="text-order-2 text-sm">Applying industry-standard QA practices to student projects, specifically in BOM verification.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black mb-4">Leadership Insight</h4>
                        <p class="text-order-2 text-sm">Utilizing supervisor-level management skills to maintain project milestones under pressure.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>